		<td><b>Balloon Fight hardware</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I recently bought a prototype of Balloon Fight which runs on NROM-128. I don't have the released version of Balloon Fight other than a ROM of it on my computer. So my question is: isn't the retail version of Balloon Fight running on NROM-256? The game code in it is quite different, but nothing in the graphics though.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Great Hierophant</b> [ Fri Apr 28, 2006 9:43 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />No, the release version of Balloon Fight uses a NROM-128 board.  The ROM size should be 24KB (16KB PRG + 8KB CHR.)  NROM-256 boards produce 40KB ROMS (32KB PRG + 8KB CHR.)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
